
# 🎓 PhD Research Proposal — Draft v0.2

**Title:**  
**Geometrically-Constrained Cytoskeletal Networks: A Unified Framework for Safe, Distributed Embodied Intelligence**

**Candidate:** ouadi Maakoul 
**Department:** Robotics & Autonomous Systems  
**Date:** October 2023  

---

## 1. 🌌 Abstract

The emergence of Vision-Language-Action (VLA) foundation models offers unprecedented generalization in robotics. However, these models lack **stability guarantees**, **safety constraints**, and **computational efficiency** for real-time deployment on dynamic systems. Current approaches treat perception, cognition, and control as disjoint pipelines, leading to error propagation and unsafe behaviors.

This thesis proposes the **Cytoskeletal Distributed Intelligence Architecture (CDIA)**. Unlike static neural networks, CDIA models robotic cognition as a **Dynamic Graph ODE**, where information pathways polymerize and depolymerize based on task demand (mimicking biological cytoskeletons). We integrate **Geometric Deep Learning** for equivariant perception and **Control Barrier Functions (CBF)** for safety-critical control.

**Core Contribution:** A mathematical framework proving that a modular, learning-based robotic system can maintain **global stability** and **forward invariance (safety)** despite switching dynamics and uncertain environments.

